(2)starting entity: The starting entity is also called salient entity, and the salient entity is the root change that causes the modification of the rest of entities in a change set, while the rest of entities are the dependency modification along with the salient one.
You will be presented with a starting entity and tools (functions) will be provided to access the more information of the origin system. Your task is to gradually explain which entity really need to be synchronized, based on the starting entity and the information obtained through the function-call. 4. **`Session.java`** and **`Database.java`**: Both have a relatively high number of supports (26 each) and similar confidence levels (~0.2016).

These entities are likely to require synchronization when changes are made to `Table.java`, given their high co-change frequency and confidence.
